cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software, please cite it as below."
title: "LISA + AutoResearch: Combined Optimization for Training Large Models on Consumer Hardware"
version: 1.0.0
date-released: 2026-03-19
url: "https://github.com/CiphemonJY/lisa-autoresearch"
authors:
  - name: "LISA + AutoResearch Contributors"
license: MIT
keywords:
  - llm
  - training
  - memory-efficient
  - disk-offload
  - lisa
  - autoresearch
  - qwen
  - mlx
  - layer-wise
  - optimization
abstract: |
  LISA + AutoResearch enables training large language models (32B+) on consumer 
  hardware (16GB RAM) using a combined optimization approach:
  
  1. LISA (Layer-wise Importance Sampling): Train only important layers, reducing 
     compute by 70-80%
  
  2. Disk-Offload: Load layer groups one at a time, storing activations on disk, 
     reducing memory by 82%
  
  3. Combined (LISA + Disk-Offload): The best of both worlds - 5x faster than 
     disk-offload alone while still fitting in 16GB RAM
  
  Memory comparison for 32B model:
    Normal:        24 GB (OOM)
    LISA only:     20 GB (OOM)  
    Disk-offload:  4.3 GB (slow)
    LISA+Offload:  5.2 GB (5x faster!)
  sampling. The AutoResearch component automatically discovers optimal
  training configurations through nightly experiments.
  
  Key features:
  - Train Qwen 7B 4-bit in ~5GB memory
  - LISA layer-wise training for memory efficiency
  - Autonomous hyperparameter discovery
  - Cross-platform support (macOS, Linux, Windows)
  
  This work builds on:
  - LISA (Layerwise Importance Sampling) - NeurIPS 2024
  - MLX framework - Apple
  - Qwen model - Qwen Team

# Dependencies
dependencies:
  - name: mlx
    version: ">=0.1.0"
  - name: mlx-lm
    version: ">=0.1.0"
  - name: transformers
    version: ">=4.30.0"

